cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI

This paper focuses on the mental models that humans form of robots and how these models affect human-robot interaction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses methods for modeling robots, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper discusses inferring human models of robots, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study conducted in the paper involves analyzing human actions, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
